name: Ron Yeats
summary: Legendary Liverpool and Tranmere Rovers captain Ron Yeats has passed away at the age of 86. The towering defender, known as "The Colossus," led Liverpool to their first FA Cup triumph in 1965 under the stewardship of Bill Shankly. Yeats also managed Tranmere Rovers and was a prominent figure in the club for many years. His later years were marked by a battle with Alzheimer's, and his death has been mourned by numerous former teammates, fans, and the football community at large.

name: England manager
summary: England's interim manager, Lee Carsley, has sparked controversy by announcing that he will not sing either the English or Irish national anthem before their upcoming match against the Republic of Ireland.
